  "prompt": "What is the processing time for Australian Visa 190?",
  "response": "The processing time for an Australian Visa 190 (Skilled Independent Visa) can vary depending on several factors, but generally:\n\n1. Average Processing Time:\n- Typically ranges from 6 to 12 months\n- Some applications may be processed faster or slower\n\n2. Factors Affecting Processing Time:\n- Completeness of application\n- Complexity of individual case\n- Current Department of Home Affairs workload\n- Accuracy of supporting documents\n- Skill assessment results\n- English language proficiency\n- Background checks\n\n3. Official Processing Time Ranges:\n- 75% of applications are usually processed within 8 months\n- 90% of applications are processed within 11 months\n\n4. Important Considerations:\n- Processing times are subject to change\n- Individual cases can differ significantly\n- Regularly check the Department of Home Affairs website for updated information\n\n5. Recommendation:\n- Submit a well-prepared, complete application\n- Ensure all documents are accurate and up-to-date\n- Include all required information to avoid delays\n\nNote: Always refer to the official Department of Home Affairs website for the most current and accurate processing time information.",
